column8:
Successfully completed requirements to become a Naval Academy Information Officer (NAIO), to include:
(a) Submission of USNA 1531/1 Naval Academy Information Program Application respective USNA BGO Area Coordinator for endorsement and approval by the USNA BGO Liaison Officer (BGOLO); 
AND
(b) Successful completion of the BGO Qualification Exam;
AND
(c) Attend formal BGO training conducted at USNA within two years of qualification.

Earned the HH2 AQD;
AND
Served as a USNA BGO Area Coordinator (AC) for at least 12 months;
AND
Been endorsed by USNA Dean of Admissions.
